Such a simple song but so much crammed into a 3 minutes 30 seconds - people underestimated Anirudh - other current music directors not able to deliver such paisa vasool songs. The verses have different chord progressions - the pre-chorus bridge are brilliant - lady singer killed it with her delivery - the muda veenai instrumental breaks are icing on the cake plus the jhumma jhumma refrain are excellent. Damn the song even includes a rap section. The movie versionâ€™s outro is awesome as well that showcases Soubinâ€™s power packed dance. Such an infectious song from Anirudh.

Soubin started his film career as an assistant director in the industry with Siddique's Chronic Bachelor (2003). He assisted directors like Fazil, Siddique, Rafi-Mecartin, P. Sukumar, Santhosh Sivan, Rajeev Ravi, and Amal Neerad.[3] He made his acting dÃ©but in Fazil's Kaiyethum Doorath (2002) while working as an assistant director. He got a breakthrough role with Alphonse Putharen's Premam (2015) where he played the role of a PT teacher. This led to his popularity as an actor in the industry.[4][5] His popular roles include in films Charlie (2015), Maheshinte Prathikaaram (2016), Kali (2016), Darvinte Parinamam (2016), Kammatipaadam (2016), Anuraga Karikkin Vellam (2016), Mayanadhi (2017), Comrade in America â€“ CIA (2017), and Kumbalangi Nights. His first full lead role was in the film Sudani from Nigeria (2018) for which he won the Kerala State Film Award for Best Actor.[6][7]  In 2024, he played the part of Siju David aka "Kuttan" in Manjummel Boys. He also produced the movie. It went on to receive critical acclaim and set several box-office records, becoming the highest grossing Malayalam film, and the first film from the industry to earn more than â‚¹200 crore.[8][9]  He is also a partner in Parava Films, a production company that has produced hits like Manjummel Boys.[10]
